## (1)(a) IETF Function and Standards

> Explain the function of the IETF (Internet Engineering Task Force) and name three of its standards. *(4 marks)*

---

The **IETF** is an open standards organization that develops and promotes **Internet standards**, particularly the TCP/IP protocol suite.

**Functions:**

- Develops technical standards for how the Internet works
- Publishes specifications as **RFCs** (Request for Comments)
- Works through open working groups (anyone can participate)

**Three IETF Standards:**

| Standard | RFC | Description |
|----------|-----|-------------|
| **IPv6** | RFC 8200 | Next-generation Internet Protocol |
| **HTTP/2** | RFC 7540 | Web protocol for faster browsing |
| **AODV** | RFC 3561 | Ad-hoc routing for MANETs |

